tags.note: Nennig Park –has a shelter and restroom facilities, four baseball diamonds, playground equipment, and basketball courts. The shelter can accommodate approx. 40 persons and has electricity available.

tags.name: Hobart Park
tags.note: (near the fairgrounds). Hobart Park has an open shelter, restroom facilities and a variety of play equipment.

tags.name: Riverside Park
tags.note: Riverside Park - 139 E. Grand St. serves as a nice, scenic sitting/resting park along the river with playground equipment

tags.name: Leahy-Lions Park
tags.note: Leahy-Lions Park – located at 139 W. Main has playground, restroom facilities and a canoe launch. The park provides scenic sitting area looking over the Manitowoc River.
